# Liftout style guide. Copy to ~/.config/liftout/style.conf and edit.
# Point these at your own brand fonts (any serif + sans .otf/.ttf) and set your
# accent colors. Anything you leave commented keeps the skill's system-font default.
# compose.sh sources this file automatically. Per-call env vars still win over it.

# Fonts (absolute paths to font files — Claude resolves these from a font name
# or website you give it; you shouldn't need to type a path here yourself)
# SERIF="/path/to/your-serif-bold.otf"      # the quote (the hero face)
# SANS="/path/to/your-sans-bold.otf"        # outlet + title
# SIT="/path/to/your-serif-italic.otf"      # byline

# Accent colors (hex). By default these are derived per-image from the hero photo's
# own dominant hue. Uncomment any of these to pin a fixed brand color instead.
# ACCENT="#e3b23c"     # accent on dark surfaces (bar, date kicker)
# CRIMSON="#a62b1f"    # accent on light surfaces
# INK="#17130e"        # the dark surface/text tone
# PAPER="#f1ece0"      # the light surface/text tone
